ined how traumatic memories of the 1997 1998 east asian financial crisis and ensuing reforms resulted in south korean leaders responding quickly and massively to the current financial crisis allowing the country to recover more rapidly than any other oecd member he also discussed future challenges to the south korean economy as it faces lagging investment an overregulated services sector and a rapidly aging society with the world's lowest birthrate co sponsored by the world affairs council of northern california and the asia foundation the event was moderated by mr philip w yun the asia foundation's vice president for resource development and a former senior us state department official the koret fellowship is generously funded by the koret foundation of of san francisco it was established to bring leading professionals in asia and the united states to stanford to study united states korea relations html+ read more world affairs council event lessons from south korea's economic policy during the global financial crisis http www itsyourworld org assnfe search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest stanford experts look at lessons learned from japan crisis march 12 2012 cisac in the news professor phillip lipscy addresses the csis japan chair forum about global reform after the financial crisis october 20 2009 shorenstein aparc news importance of us south korea relations in dealing with north korea shorenstein aparc ksp in the news korea times san francisco on september 25 2009 national security the g20 and the global financial crisis cisac in the news democracy arsenal on april 1 2009 south africa's electricity crisis february 22 2008 pesd news north korea and contending south korean identities analysis of the south korean media policy implications for the united states may 9 2007 shorenstein aparc ksp news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institut